05/04/2004
TOKYO, Japan -- A one-day economic and security conference on the Balkans opened in Tokyo on Monday (5 April). 
Ministers from Albania, Bosnia and Herzegovina, Croatia, Macedonia, and Serbia-Montenegro joined representatives of 38 countries, including Russia, the United States and Canada, as well as the EU and 12 international organisations. 
Japanese Foreign Minister Yoriko Kawaguchi told delegates that the conference highlights the international community's continuing commitment to the Balkans. 
She stressed that economic development would be impossible without ethnic reconciliation and peace. 
Separately, Albania is to announce its decision to open an embassy mission in Japan, aimed at enhancing bilateral ties. 
(AFP - 05/04/04; ATA - 04/04/04)
